ar dependency (A1 references B1, B1 references A1) and returns a circular reference error instead of looping.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Circular dependency detection is a local graph algorithm (cycle detection). A unit test that sets up circular references and verifies an error is raised (not stack overflow or infinite loop) will catch all cycle-detection bugs. No I/O, subprocess, or external dependencies.","test_description":"Create in-memory cells A1==B1+1 and B1==A1+1. Attempt to evaluate A1. Verify a 'circular reference' error is raised. Test longer cycles (A1 → B1 → C1 → A1), self-references (A1==A1+1), and cycles through cross-sheet references if supported.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.05,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"VLOOKUP with an exact match returns the correct value from the lookup table, and returns an error when the key is not found.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"VLOOKUP is a table lookup function operating on in-memory lookup tables. A unit test that creates lookup tables and verifies correct matches and error handling will catch VLOOKUP logic bugs (wrong column, type coercion, missing keys). No I/O or external dependencies.","test_description":"Create an in-memory lookup table (names and values). Call VLOOKUP for a key that exists and verify correct value returned. Call VLOOKUP for a key that does not exist and verify 'value not found' error. Test different data types, table sizes, duplicate keys, case sensitivity, and empty tables.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.98,"Integration":0.02,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The IF function correctly handles nested conditions (e.g., =IF(A1>10, IF(A1>20, \"high\", \"medium\"), \"low\")).","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Nested IF tests the expression parser and conditional evaluator. A unit test with in-memory cells and various nested IF expressions will catch bugs in condition evaluation, operator precedence, or nesting logic. No I/O or external dependencies.","test_description":"Create in-memory cell A1=15. Evaluate =IF(A1>10, IF(A1>20, \"high\", \"medium\"), \"low\") and verify result is \"medium\". Test multiple nesting depths, different operators (>, <, ==, !=), type coercion, null/empty branches, and deeply nested structures.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.98,"Integration":0.02,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"CONCATENATE joins cell values with the correct separator and handles empty cells by skipping them rather than inserting blank strings.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"CONCATENATE is a string operation on in-memory cell values. A unit test that sets up cells with various values (including empty) and verifies the join skips empty cells will catch empty-cell-handling bugs (inserting blanks, type coercion errors). No I/O or external dependencies.","test_description":"Create in-memory cells A1=\"Hello\", A2=\"\", A3=\"World\". Evaluate =CONCATENATE(A1, A2, A3) and verify result is \"HelloWorld\" (not \"Hello World\" or \"Hello  World\"). Test different separators if supported, all-empty ranges, single-cell ranges, and type conversion (numbers, dates, booleans).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.05,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"A formula referencing a cell in a different sheet (e.g., =Sheet2!A1+1) resolves correctly when the referenced sheet exists.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Cross-sheet references require the formula parser to handle sheet prefixes and the evaluator to look up sheets and cells. A unit test with in-memory sheets will catch bugs in sheet lookup, reference parsing, or cell resolution. All operations are in-process, in-memory.","test_description":"Create in-memory sheets: Sheet1 with A1=5, Sheet2 with A1=10. In Sheet1, evaluate =Sheet2!A1+1 and verify result is 11. Test non-existent sheets (expect error), invalid cell references, cyclic cross-sheet references, and sheet names with special characters or spaces.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"When a referenced cell's value changes, all dependent formulas are recalculated in the correct topological order.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Topological recalculation tests the dependency graph and invalidation strategy. A unit test that modifies a cell and verifies all dependents are recalculated with fresh values (not stale cached values) will catch bugs in cache invalidation or evaluation order. All operations are in-process, in-memory.","test_description":"Create in-memory cells: A1=5, B1==A1*2, C1==B1+10, D1==A1+C1. Change A1 to 10 and recalculate. Verify B1=20, C1=30, D1=40 (each using fresh dependency values). Test with more complex graphs, multiple independent branches, and cells with multiple dependencies.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"The undo operation after editing a formula restores both the formula text and all previously computed dependent values.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Undo is an in-process state management feature. A unit test that edits a formula, triggers undo, and verifies the formula text and dependent values are restored will catch bugs in state capture, snapshot restoration, or recalculation after restore. No I/O or external dependencies are required for the core test.","test_description":"Create in-memory cells A1=5, B1==A1*2. Edit B1 to ==A1*3 and verify B1 now evaluates to 15. Undo the edit and verify B1 formula is ==A1*2 and evaluates to 10. Test undo/redo sequences, multiple edits, cross-cell edits, and boundary cases (undo at history start